President Biden visited Earth Rider Brewery in Superior, Wisconsin to discuss the progress being made in investing in America and American workers. He highlighted the recent positive consumer sentiment about the economy and the record number of new business applications. He also emphasized the growth of the economy and the low inflation rate, debunking claims of an impending recession. President Biden announced a $1 billion investment from the Bipartisan Infrastructure Law to build a new bridge connecting Minnesota to Wisconsin, creating 10,000 new construction jobs. He also mentioned investments in high-speed internet, clean water, and the elimination of lead pipes. President Biden criticized the previous administration's approach to the economy, highlighting the outsourcing of jobs and the unfair tax system. He pledged to make the tax system more equitable and ensure that pharmaceutical corporations charge fair prices for medications. President Biden concluded by expressing optimism about the future of America and the capacity to overcome challenges when working together.